Remarks: The dispensary was not open that day. But it operates. The water conveyance/pipeline is vandalized. The dispensary fetches water from the borehole via a hired vehicle.
The dispensary requires more storage tanks and connection water. The dispensary person incharge should train the community health works and TBAs.
We were not able to get the information because the nurse incharge was not there. Information needs verification.

The community requires a lot of education in water treatment because common health problems like diarrhoea, eye infections and skin infections are there due to scarcity of safe water for domestic use. This can be achieved through seminars to community leaders, CHW, TBAs and village water commitees. The facility also requires more storage tanks and piping work within the compound.
The dispensary is still new. It has not been opened. So no information is got. Awaiting staffing. International Medical Corps have given equipment. Constructed by ALRMP.
Not able to get full information about the common diseases because of insecurity and were depending on the kenya military army. There is need for incinerator for disposing used needles.

The Lolmolog dispensary had a problem of a nurse. The nurse who was posted here has not reported for 9 months. So nobody to gave information about the common diseases and other facilities inside the dispesary.
The nurse incharge was not around when we visited the dispensary so we have not got the full information about the dispensary.
Didn't meet the nurse so couldn't get number of diseases. We met a community member/teacher/management committee.
The dispensary is not operating, because it is a new dispensary not yet registered with M.O.H.
The dispensary has no toilet and incinerator which is a very essential thing in the facility.
The hospital requires completion of peadiatric hall to prevent congestion in the maternity all. The hospital compound was fenced and partitioned to control movement of people around.
Were unable to get the common disease because the nurse was not there.
We are unable to get the info on common diseases because the nurse with documents was not around.
The dispensary need water connected inside the compound.
The dispensary requires more storage tanks, incinerator and toilets.
The dispensary is closed so we were unable to capture information (the nurse was not posted). It is a community dispensary and not yet registered by the MOH.
The dispensary is still under construction.

The dispensary is well kept but requires water. The borehole is not far but the dispensary lacks piped water. There is no refrigerator for vaccines hence no immunization services.  It would be appropriate if they get gas controlled fridge.

There is no fence around the facility premises making it difficult to maintain hygiene hence the need to be provided. The facility serves clients coming from far making it necessary to start a mobile clinic.
Well kept health centre as in records and services provision.
Well kept dispensary in terms of records and service provision.
Well kept but a room for storing drugs and other supplementary kits is needed.
Well kept dispensary, only water is a major problem. Sand dams are approprite, silting in Seiya seasonal rivers.

The facility/in charge would wish to have a radio communication due to barriers and referrals, a staff house, power source(solar), additional latrines, repair of ferrocement tank that is currently leaking hence not in use. A fence is also advisable to protect vandalism by the surrounding community.
The health centre well kept but water is the big problem in facility.

Well maintained dispensary only requires basic facilities such as water tank for storage and toilets, radio communication is required to enhance communication during referral in that it is very remote.
The hospital has a plan to construct a VCT. The water needs treatment before use. The place where the water is accessed at the river is poor making the water dirty and not very clean for consumption.
The information given for data is reliable.
The information given is reliable.
The staff is very insufficient and so the government should increase the staffing.
More nurses and patient attendants are required.
The facility needs an alternative water source and additional staff to cater for the number of people in the community.

The records for the common diseases cannot be reached for all the diseases since the records are readmitted to Marsabit district. The dispensary needs an alternitive water source since the primary source is not very reliable.
